<p>Sophia Connell, currently reader in philosophy at <a href="https://www.bbk.ac.uk/school/historical-studies/study-philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Birkbeck, University of London</a>, will be moving to the <a href="https://philosophy.nd.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Notre Dame</a>, where she will be associate professor of philosophy.<span id="more-54167"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-54169 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/connell-sophia.jpeg" alt="" width="400" height="600" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/connell-sophia.jpeg 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/connell-sophia-200x300.jpeg 200w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p>Dr. Connell specializes in ancient Greek philosophy, especially Aristotle, and has also written on the role of women in the history of philosophy. She is the author of<em>Â Aristotle on Women: Physiology, Psychology, and Politics</em> (2021) and <em>Aristotle on Female Animals: A Study of the Generation of Animals</em> (2015), among other works, which you can learn more about <a href="https://www.bbk.ac.uk/our-staff/profile/9146754/sophia-m-connell" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/sophia-connell" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>She takes up her new position at Notre Dame in January, 2026.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/06/23/connell-from-birkbeck-to-notre-dame/">Connell from Birkbeck to Notre Dame</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>